'''Chivalry'''

#An ethical code that was prevalent in Medieval [[Europe]].  It was the honor code of the [[knight]]s.

It's primary virtues were:
* [[Mercy]] (Towards the poor and oppressed. They were supposed to be harsh with evil-doers.)
* [[Humility]]
* [[Honor]]
* [[Sacrifice]]
* Fear of [[God]]
* [[Faithfulness]]
* [[Courage]]
* Utmost graciousness and courtesy to ladies

